# Licensing Guidelines

## Overview
Standards for software licensing and copyright management across the project.

## Configuration
globs: ["LICENSE*", "*.py", "*.sql", "*.sh", "*.md"]
priority: critical

## Rules

### License Selection
1. Open Source Requirements
   - Use MIT License for public repositories
   - Include copyright notice
   - Include permission notice
   - Include warranty disclaimer
   - Keep license text unmodified

2. Third-Party Dependencies
   - Check compatibility with project license
   - Document all licenses in README
   - Keep track of license obligations
   - Review license changes in updates

### License Headers
1. Source Code Files
   - Include copyright notice
   - Include license reference
   - Keep headers up to date
   - Use consistent format

2. Documentation
   - Include license information
   - Reference third-party content
   - Specify usage restrictions
   - Include attribution notices

